In short:

- The agent that runs on customer machines is Apache 2.0. Anyone can fork,
  modify, redistribute, embed in their own products, and use it commercially
  with no obligation other than preserving copyright and license notices.

- The shared Netmaker wrapper library used by both the admin and the agent
  is Apache 2.0 on the same terms.

- The admin server is licensed under the Elastic License 2.0. You can read,
  modify, and self-host it freely. The license restricts offering Edge Admin
